[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1472[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mA note on calibration drift. Calibration is typically the first thing to break in production. A model that was perfectly calibrated at deployment time slowly drifts as the workforce composition changes (new hires, retirements, role changes), as the EHR upgrades change click paths, and as the rule library evolves. SageMaker Model Monitor catches this when ground-truth labels arrive, but the lag between the drift and the labels means that operational thresholds can be wrong for weeks before the monitor notices. Production programs run a parallel "shadow" calibration fit on the most recent labeled cases and alert when the shadow calibration disagrees substantially with the deployed calibration. The shadow gives a faster signal than waiting for the formal Model Monitor cadence.[K
