[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The Python companion at chapter03.09-python-example.md fully implements the eight pseudocode steps end-to-end (ingest/normalize, enrich, rules-engine, baseline detector, graph detector, composite scoring, case-builder, outcome capture) with a runnable demo invocation. boto3 usage is correct: typed clients/resources are constructed with adaptive retry Config; calls use proper kwargs (kinesis.put_record with StreamName/Data/PartitionKey, dynamodb Table.get_item/put_item/update_item/query/scan with Key and UpdateExpression/ExpressionAttributeValues, s3.put_object with Bucket/Key/Body/ServerSideEncryption, cloudwatch.put_metric_data with Namespace/MetricData, eventbridge.put_events with Entries containing Source/DetailType/Detail/EventBusName, sagemaker_runtime.invoke_endpoint with EndpointName/ContentType/Body, bedrock_runtime.invoke_model with modelId/body and Anthropic message schema). Error-handling commentary and patterns are present: adaptive retry config is explained, try/except around Bedrock invocation falls back to a structured narrative and emits a CloudWatch failure metric, metric emission itself is wrapped in try/except, and Decimal conversion is documented to prevent float-drift bugs in DynamoDB threshold comparisons. The simplifications (in-process NetworkX graph, local sklearn model, synthetic seed data, geolocate_ip placeholder, family-link/household lookups returning False) are explicitly framed as teaching substitutions for production AWS components rather than incomplete work, and each is paired with a documented production swap (Neptune Gremlin query, score_via_sagemaker_endpoint helper, real EMPI/IAM mappings). The pipeline trains a real logistic regression with isotonic calibration, scores synthetic events, persists cases to DynamoDB with EventBridge fan-out, and writes labels to S3, satisfying the end-to-end recipe pattern requirement."}[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[32mAll tools are now trusted ([0m[